**4.3.1.1** To reduce direct glare in industrial areas, the following steps should be taken:
a) Decrease the luminance of light sources or lighting equipment, or both;
b) Reduce the area of high luminance causing the glare condition;
c) Increase the angle between the glare source and the line of vision; and
d) Increase the luminance of the area surrounding the glare source and against which it is seen.

